"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1929477-Olympics-2024-Ana-Carolina-Vieira\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Brazilian swimmer Ana Carolina Vieira has broken her silence after she was sent home from the2024 Olympics, claiming that previous complaints of harassment within the team had been ignored.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 39, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ana_Carolina_Vieira\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ana Carolina Vieira\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ana_Carolina_Vieira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ana_Carolina_Vieira\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old has aimed fire at the Brazilian Olympic Committee (COB) over the manner of her expulsion.\", \"from\": 192, \"to\": 297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 230, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brazilian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 259, \"end\": 262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.2803299521357795e-24, \"text\": \"COB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vieira competed on Saturday with Brazil's 4x100 metres freestyle relay team, finishing 12th in the heats.\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9999993883163422, \"rank\": 5.883450311233089e-07, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, on Sunday, the COB confirmed that it had sent her home from the Paris Games after she left the Olympic village without permission.\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 426, \"end\": 429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.2803299521357795e-24, \"text\": \"COB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pick up your ultimate guide to the Olympics!\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Going for Gold provides the day-by-day rundown of what's on and when.\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clickhereto buy.\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Teammate Gabriel Santos - who received a warning for her behaviour - was also involved, with the pair's social media activity revealing their whereabouts.\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 685, \"end\": 699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Santos_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9999963865517913, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Santos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Santos_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Santos_(swimmer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The BOC revealed it was informed by Gustavo Otsuka, the head of Brazil's swimming team, and added that Vieira challenged the formation of the relay.\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 836, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999749889, \"rank\": 2.4702938463829404e-11, \"text\": \"BOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpe